There are several options to save the embattled national carrier. eNCA has obtained a draft plan, setting out what's being discussed and considered to save SAA. The preliminary plan is in effect what business rescue practitioners, are weighing up as ways to move forward. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - There are several options to save the embattled national carrier, South African Airways. eNCA has obtained a draft plan, setting out what's being discussed and considered to save SAA. READ: Court denies Airlink right to sue SAA The preliminary plan is in effect what business rescue practitioners are weighing up as ways to move forward. The 53-page draft document points out different scenarios that could be followed.